buyRaffleTicket(uint256,uint128).notice: Allows users to buy tickets for a Raffle

params._numberOfTickets: The number of tickets an user wants to buy
params._raffleId: The ID of the raffle the user wants to buy a ticket for

buyWhitelistedRaffleTicket(uint256,uint1.notice: Allows users to buy tickets for a whitelisted Raffle

params._merkleProof: MerkleProof used to verify user is aprt of the whitelist
params._numberOfTickets: The number of tickets an user wants to buy
params._raffleId: The ID of the raffle the user wants to buy a ticket for

cancelRaffle(uint256).notice: Allows users to cancel a raffle if NO tickets were sold yet

claimCancelledRaffle(uint256,uint256[]).notice: Allows users to claim a cancelled raffle where they will receive their initially payment plus 0.1 Ether

params._raffleId: The ID of the raffle the user wants to buy a ticket for

claimRaffle(uint256).notice: Allows users to claim the raffle. Owner of the raffle will receive the payment and the winner his asset

params._raffleId: The ID of the raffle the user wants to buy a ticket for

completeRaffle(uint256).notice: Allows users to complete a Raffle. The winner of the raffle will receive the asset. The owner of the raffle will receive his payment Cron job will call daily all the pending raffles. Users can also call it

params._raffleId: The ID of the raffle the user wants to buy a ticket for

createERC20Raffle(address,uint256,addres.notice: Allows users to create a raffle of an ERC20 asset

params._amount: Quantity of tokens to be raffled
params._currency: Tickets will be bought with this ERC20 token. address(0) should be put here if the currency will be Ether
params._durationInSeconds: Duration in seconds of the raffle
params._merkleRoot: Used so only whitelisted users can buy raffle tickets
params._minimumTicketsSold: Number of tickets that should be sold in order to be a success raffle. If this minimum amount is not reached the owner of the raffle will be able to cancel the raffle, returning the users their payment plus a little collateral to cover for the gas fees. If this amount is reached, normal flow will be followed
params._numberOfTickets: Number of tickets that will be sold as maximum in the raffle
params._pricePerTicket: Price per ticket. It can be zero in case of an "airdrop"
params._tokenAddress: Address of the token amount to raffle

createERC721Raffle(address,uint256,addre.notice: Allows users to create a raffle of an ERC721 asset

params._currency: Tickets will be bought with this ERC20 token. address(0) should be put here if the currency will be Ether
params._durationInSeconds: Duration in seconds of the raffle
params._merkleRoot: Used so only whitelisted users can buy raffle tickets
params._minimumTicketsSold: Number of tickets that should be sold in order to be a success raffle. If this minimum amount is not reached the owner of the raffle will be able to cancel the raffle, returning the users their payment plus a little collateral to cover for the gas fees. If this amount is reached, normal flow will be followed.
params._nftCollection: Address of the NFT to raffle
params._numberOfTickets: Number of tickets that will be sold as maximum in the raffle
params._pricePerTicket: Price per ticket. It can be zero in case of an "airdrop"
